<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--ChinaTV     10-08 0151</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--China TV,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>China Has 600 Million Television Watchers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Once the world's largest untapped source of
television viewers, China now boasts nearly 60 percent viewership
among its 1.08 billion people.
   National radio and television officials reported at a seminar
this week in Beijing that 600 million Chinese watch television
daily, the official China Daily said today.
   China now has 116 million television sets, 37 times more than a
decade ago, with an average of one set for every 10 people.
   The national and international news program broadcast by China
Central Television Station now reaches 42 percent of the population
each evening, the paper said.
   The country's 118 television assembly lines have a combined
annual production of 15 million. But demand for televisions,
particularly color sets, far outstrips supply, Xinhua said. Figures
were not available for the number of sets imported annually, but
Japanese brands are very popular.
</TEXT>
