Western Samoa.
   It said the quake was recorded at 12.59 p.m. There were no other
details.
   The Richter scale is a guage of energy released by an
earthquake, as measured by ground motion recorded on a seismograph.
   An earthquake of magnitude 6 can cause severe damage.
