   Siegfried and Roy may be able to make an
elephant disappear on stage, but the illusionists can't get their
225 tons of equipment to Japan quite so magically.
   Accompanying the pair on an eight-month stint in Tokyo will be
computerized laser lights, a stage one-third the length of a
football field, 125 cast and crew members, and a menagerie of
lions, panthers, leopards and rare white tigers used in their
popular show.
   Siegfried and Roy have entertained millions of showgoers since
they opened their act ``Beyond Belief'' on the Las Vegas Strip.
