<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Hungary-Union     10-08 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Hungary-Union,0180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Third Independent Union Formed In Hungary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A new trade federation for education
workers was created Saturday, making it the third independent union
to be established in Communist Hungary since May, the state news
agency MTI reported.
   The news agency said 195 delegates attended the founding meeting
on behalf of the 30,000 Hungarian teachers employed in higher
education.
   According to its draft constitution, the new union is to be an
independent, democratic organization so it can more effectively
represent teaching professionals, the agency said.
   Delegates were reported to have criticized the ``hierarchic and
bureaucratic character'' of former trade unions and poor pay and
working conditions in the field. They also warned of the danger of
underestimating teachers' scholarly work, MTI said.
   Filmmakers, television and video art workers earlier this month
set up an independent Motion Picture Democratic Union called MODESZ.
   The first independent union, the Democratic Union of Scientific
Workers, was founded in May following widespread complaints about
official unions' failure to prevent cuts in state subsidies for
academic work.
</TEXT>
