<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Frank Emig</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Frank W. Emig, director of the AFL-CIO's
department of community services since 1985, died Saturday from
cancer. He was 62.
   Emig previously headed the labor federation's efforts to stop
the spread of state right-to-work laws.
   As director of community services, Emig headed a network of
representatives in 188 cities in 37 states responsible for
coordinating blood drives, food banks and other charities,
according to Rex Hardesty, a federation spokesman.
